				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Gear Check<a name="35321"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 18 04 10:07 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Are you a solo bard only? Do you group at all? are you in a small guild? 
<br />

<br />
Sorry not trying to be super annoying, but it effects on what I would point out for upgrades.
<br />

<br />

<br />
My biggest and obvious upgrade I would suggest -- and it should be predictable!
<br />

<br />
Cloak of Greater Perncity. Great cha, some other good stats, 50 HP/Mana.
<br />

<br />
If you are a bard that groups often, take a group of friends and go camp a soulscream belt in Veksar. Very small quarters, named summons so I don't think that puts him on a soloable list, but don't quote me on that.
<br />

<br />
Upstairs from the rotting shopkeeper is another named, but nothing that would be an upgrade. When you are done getting soulscream belts (and many kunzar deathshields) Go upstairs and drop down. There will be odd looking mobs again, but this time, the ones in front of you, randomly drop Klyong Darkmail gaunts. Goooooood gloves.  Drops quite often even.
<br />

<br />
(If you wish to feel safer, behind you at this point, is a ramp. Go over that ramp and you're back real close to zone in. It's 1 way.)
<br />

<br />
There's a nice range in Mischief that you can try to get. Amusing Bauble, some more HP and good resists (please excuse me, I'm an HP addict).
<br />

<br />
Uhm, wow there's a lot of earrings out there these days ya know. There's a lot to suggest from, but maybe I should stop because I'm looking at this from the perspective of a bard who groups way more than solos.
<br />

<br />

<br />
I'm a cheap person. I like to hunt for my gear rather than buy it if possible. Sometimes, I get lazy and just buy stuff ;)
<br />

<br />

<br />
Hmm necklace. Well, with my suggestions, you would lose a lot of dex... you can ignore me, really. Maybe uhm.. oh darn what's it called..  Oh yes, Darkwater Pearl Necklace. I hear it's a good neck piece.
<br />

<br />
Perhaps a Ring of Thunderous Spirits? (THey're pretty darn cheap on my server actually)
<br />

<br />
Okay, well thats my suggestions =.)</span></td>
