				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Gear Check<a name="35409"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 19 04 10:53 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>If I recall the late 50s correctly, you should be entering the time where you're grouping/pulling/CC and need better AC/HP and Resists (and possibly CHA, although I found I needed to improve CHA around lvl 62 or so).
<br />

<br />
I'd suggest a few upgrades:
<br />

<br />
Neck - Amulet of Mummy Wrappings, Ribbon Choker, Necklace of Flame Marked Links
<br />

<br />
Earring - Bloodmetal Earring of Engagement, Architect's
<br />

<br />
Wrists - Beauty, Rock Molded
<br />

<br />
Hands - Kylong Darkmail
<br />

<br />
Rings - Lots of choices here including some very nice LDoN items, but the 6/65s are not a glaring weakness.
<br />

<br />
Cloak - Moss-Covered Cape; Crinose Cape, Defender's Cloak (cheap). 
<br />

<br />
While others will disagree, I didn't find the need for a haste item until quite recently, when I purchased a 31% augment for my belt and then received a Cape of Broken Enchantments from a high risk LDoN in EF.  A lot depends upon your style of play and the weaponry you use.  If you spend a lot of your time pulling and Crowd Controlling, then haste and weapons are not a primarly concern.  In fact, you may be using your drums primary more often for debuffing mobs. 
<br />

<br />

<br />

